# Cursor Configuration Rules

## Package Management

- Always use YARN instead of npm
- Use `yarn add` for installing packages
- Use `yarn remove` for uninstalling packages
- Use `yarn install` for installing dependencies
- Use `yarn dev` for development server
- Use `yarn build` for building the project
- Use `yarn start` for starting the production server

## Code Style

- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use modern React patterns (hooks, functional components)
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add proper TypeScript types

## File Organization

- Keep components in appropriate directories
- Use consistent file naming conventions
- Group related functionality together
- Maintain clean import/export structure
